  "text": "53 VSNL1 was reported to be highly expressed in the rat adrenal ZG, to be upregulated in APAs, [CITATION_1] and to be acutely downregulated by the adrenocorticotropic hormone. [CITATION_2] APAs harboring KCNJ5 mutations overexpress VSNL1 compared with wild-type APAs, resulting in inhibition of Ca 2+ -induced apoptosis. The role(s) of VSNL1 in adrenal ZG physiology, and whether it is a marker of aldosterone-producing and APA cells, remains to be fully explored.",
